spring quarters in summer tuition allowance for a ta covers three units tas are hired by the department and receive a payroll check twice a month in addition to a health insurance subsidy tas work an average of 20 hours per week during the quarter in which they are employed if you are an international student working as a ta for the first time you must obtain language clearance from the linguistics department by taking the oral english proficiency test given by the english for foreign student efs staff prior to starting the ta position http www stanford edu group efs tascreen html payroll dates for ras and tas quarter span first check last check autumn oct 1 dec 31 oct 22 jan 7 winter jan 1 mar 31 jan 22 apr 7 spring apr 1 jun 30 apr 22 jul 7 summer jul 1 sep 30 jul 22 oct 7 limit on hours for us students during autumn winter and spring quarters students on 50 percent time assistantships may not be employed more that an additional eight hours per week inside stanford and or outside of stanford those eight hours cannot be in other assistantship positions limit on hours for international students students on f 1 and j 1 visas are limited to a total of 20 hours of employment on campus per week including their assistantship appointment s during any quareter in which they are fully enrolled for further information regarding regulations for students with f 1 and j 1 visas contact bechtel international center http www stanford edu dept icenter additional funding sources stanford funding sources stanford graduate research opportunities gro & travel funds stanford lieberman fellowship siepr fellowships olin law & economics fellowships & research awards economics department distinguished ta award cisac fellowships nsf robert wood johnson foundation scholars in health policy research bls dissertation fellowship student payroll at stanford comprehensive exam archive up student payroll at stanford stanford university economics department 579 serra mall stanford ca 94305 6072 650